Let me extract the text from the PDF and find the Introduction section. I'll use a Python script in the terminal.

```python
import pyautogui
import time

# Type a command to extract text and find Introduction section
pyautogui.typewrite("python3 -c \"\nimport subprocess\nresult = subprocess.run(['pdftotext', '/root/Desktop/GE Guidebook.pdf', '-'], capture_output=True, text=True)\ntext = result.stdout\nlines = text.split('\\n')\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines[:200]):\n    print(f'{i}: {line}')\n\"", interval=0.02)

# Actually, let me use a simpler approach - write a script file
pyautogui.hotkey('ctrl', 'c')
time.sleep(0.3)

# Let me write a Python script to extract and examine the PDF
cmd = """python3 << 'EOF'
import subprocess
result = subprocess.run(['pdftotext', '/root/Desktop/GE Guidebook.pdf', '/tmp/ge_guidebook.txt'], capture_output=True, text=True)
print("Exit code:", result.returncode)
print("Stderr:", result.stderr)
with open('/tmp/ge_guidebook.txt', 'r') as f:
    text = f.read()
lines = text.split('\\n')
for i, line in enumerate(lines[:300]):
    print(f"{i}: {line}")
EOF
"""
pyautogui.typewrite(cmd, interval=0.01)
time.sleep(0.5)
pyautogui.press('enter')
time.sleep(3)
```

