paragraph		The Thunderbird Desktop, Thunderbird for iOS, Thunderbird for Android, and K-9 Mail applications (together, “Thunderbird”) allow users to privately integrate and manage their online communications. K-9 Mail is a variant of Thunderbird for Android. All references to “Thunderbird” or “Thunderbird for Android” apply equally to K-9 Mail.			(488, 407)	(640, 100)
paragraph		This Privacy Notice explains what data Thunderbird collects and shares, and why. We also adhere to the  for how we receive, handle, and share information.			(488, 527)	(640, 60)
link	Mozilla Privacy Policy	Mozilla Privacy Policy			(661, 548)	(171, 19)
paragraph		This privacy notice is for the most recent general release version of Thunderbird distributed by MZLA Technologies Corporation (a subsidiary of Mozilla Foundation). If you obtain Thunderbird elsewhere, or are running an older version, your copy of Thunderbird may contain different privacy characteristics.			(488, 607)	(640, 80)
heading	Thunderbird Collects Data To:	Thunderbird Collects Data To:			(488, 781)	(848, 42)
heading	Improve Performance, Stability, and Functionality For Our Users	Improve Performance, Stability, and Functionality For Our Users			(488, 855)	(848, 31)
paragraph		Thunderbird sends telemetry about your interactions with Thunderbird to us. There are two types of telemetry data: interaction data and technical data.			(488, 918)	(848, 40)
paragraph		Interaction data: Thunderbird receives measurements about how you use Thunderbird and how well it’s working, such as, whether calendars and filters are being used, and how many email accounts a user has.			(488, 978)	(848, 40)
paragraph		Technical data: Thunderbird also receives environment data from your device, such as, application version, hardware configuration, device operating system, and language preference. When Thunderbird sends technical data to us, your IP address is temporarily collected as part of our server logs.			(488, 1038)	(848, 60)
